import React from "react";
import { Container, Row, Col, Card } from "react-bootstrap";

function Cards() {
  return (
    <Container>
      <Row className="my-4">
        <Col md={4}>
          <Card style={{ backgroundColor: "#f0f8ff", borderColor: "#add8e6" }}>
            <Card.Body>
              <Card.Title tag="h5">First Card</Card.Title>
              <Card.Text>
                Some quick example text to build on the first card title and make
                up the bulk of the card's content.
              </Card.Text>
              <Card.Link href="#">First Link</Card.Link>
              <Card.Link href="#">Second Link</Card.Link>
            </Card.Body>
          </Card>
        </Col>
        <Col md={4}>
          <Card style={{ backgroundColor: "#f5f5dc", borderColor: "#deb887" }}>
            <Card.Body>
              <Card.Title tag="h5">Second Card</Card.Title>
              <Card.Text>
                Some quick example text to build on the second card title and make
                up the bulk of the card's content.
              </Card.Text>
              <Card.Link href="#">First Link</Card.Link>
              <Card.Link href="#">Second Link</Card.Link>
            </Card.Body>
          </Card>
        </Col>
        <Col md={4}>
          <Card style={{ backgroundColor: "#e6e6fa", borderColor: "#9370db" }}>
            <Card.Body>
              <Card.Title tag="h5">Third Card</Card.Title>
              <Card.Text>
                Some quick example text to build on the third card title and make
                up the bulk of the card's content.
              </Card.Text>
              <Card.Link href="#">First Link</Card.Link>
              <Card.Link href="#">Second Link</Card.Link>
            </Card.Body>
          </Card>
        </Col>
      </Row>
    </Container>
  );
}

export default Cards;
